This paper proposes a new training objective for neural networks that combines the power of neural networks and label propagation on graphs. The paper focuses on semi-supervised learning, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The experiments conducted in the paper involve multi-label classification on social graphs, news categorization, and semantic intent classification, which are all related to natural language processing and computational linguistics. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper involves text classification, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper proposes a new training objective that can be trained efficiently using stochastic gradient descent, which is a common optimization technique in neural networks and falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
